{"lemma":"مَعاشِ","slug":"مَعاشِ","root":"ع.#.ش","root_slug":"ع-_-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَعاش","root":"عيش","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31222"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B4%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَاشَ (ʕāša) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"livelihood, subsistence","examples":[{"text":"وَأَكْثَرُ مَا يَحْمِلُ عَلَى ٱلْتِمَاسِ هٰذِهِ الصِّنَاعَةِ وَٱنْتِحَالِهَا هُوَ كَمَا قُلْنَاهُ الْعَجْزُ عَنِ الطُّرُقِ الطَّبِيعِيَّةِ لِلْمَعَاشِ وَٱبْتِغَاؤُهُ مِنْ غَيْرِ وُجُوهِهِ الطَّبِيعِيَّةِ كَٱلْفِلَاحَةِ وَٱلتِّجَارَةِ وَٱلصِّنَاعَةِ فَيَسْتَصْعِبُ الْعَاجِزُ ٱبْتِغَاءَهُ مِنْ هٰذِهِ وَيَرُومُ الْحُصُولَ عَلَى الْكَثِيرِ مِنَ الْمَالِ دُفْعَةً بِوُجُوهٍ غَيْرِ طَبِيعِيَّةٍ مِنَ الْكِيمِيَاءِ وَغَيْرِهَا.","english":"The most common cause of the desire to practice alchemy is, as we have stated; a person’s inability to make his living in a natural way and the wish to make a living in some way that, unlike agriculture, commerce, and (handi)craft, is not natural. A person without ability finds it difficult to make his living in such (legitimate occupations). He wants to get rich all at once through some (occupation) that is not natural, such as alchemy and other things."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"salary","tags":["post-Classical"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ma.ʕaːʃ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31222","headword_ar":"مَعَاشٌ","root":"Ey$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiy$N","text_ar":"مَعِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be used as substantives as well as inf. ns., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAbN","text_ar":"مَعَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiybN","text_ar":"مَعِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, TA;) and signify, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiy$apN","text_ar":"مَعِيشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That whereby one lives:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which one lives:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or rather, they have both these significations; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mEA$","text_ar":"معاش"},{"kind":"text","text":"has generally the latter. whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mEy$p","text_ar":"معيشة"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mEy$","text_ar":"معيش"},{"kind":"text","text":", are generally used in the former sense, or one similar to it:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaA$N","text_ar":"مَعَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of subsistence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usual, place thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time wherein one seeks sustenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Thus, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaA$u Alxaloqi","text_ar":"مَعَاشُ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth is the place of subsistence of mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the created beings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ahaAru maEaA$N","text_ar":"النَّهَارُ مَعَاشٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day is the time for seeking sustenance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur, lxxviii. 11. (O, TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiy$apN","text_ar":"مَعِيشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2211}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}